# mstack frontend

## Structure

- Prefer **small, composable** components; colocate styles and tests when the repo does.
- **Named exports** if that is the repo convention; otherwise follow existing files.

## UI quality

- Clear **typography scale** and spacing rhythm; align to design tokens if present.
- **Semantic HTML**; meaningful labels; no div-only interactive controls.
- **Responsive**: mobile-first unless the product dictates otherwise.

## State & data

- Handle **loading and errors** at boundaries; avoid silent failures.
- Avoid unnecessary client-side waterfalls; prefer patterns already used in the repo (RSC, loaders, etc.).

## Performance

- Lazy-load heavy routes or widgets when the stack supports it.
- Memoize only when measured or obviously expensive; do not blanket `useMemo`.

## Anti-slop checklist

- [ ] Distinct visual hierarchy (not everything centered gray-on-gray).
- [ ] Real copy or realistic placeholders (not “Lorem” for final review).
- [ ] Focus states visible; motion justified.

For research phase, see `mstack-design-research.mdc`.
